  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When a plugin imports something from hardhat, it can import both from `hardhat/foo` and from `hardhat/src/foo`, but only the first one is correct. The second one works, but it can cause some issues (see #2260, for example).\r\n\r\nMore generally, we should forbid _any_ import that starts with `package/src` or `@org/package/src`.",
